command_block.28.command.5: Songs of Greavesoyl is Team PVP map set in dark fantasy universe of my comic series. With 2 teams fighting for the victory, many varied characters to play and learn, multiple maps to choose you and your friends can have endless fun playing both casually and competitively.
command_block.28.command.7: In the lobby you can change the map, amount of points required to win, see your statistics and well... start the game. Click on the signs
command_block.28.command.10: After starting the game players are assigned to teams randomly. You pick the character by entering the iron door.
command_block.28.command.11: You can click on the sign to see summary of the character
command_block.28.command.12: . Detailed descriptions are avaible in-game and on the wiki.
command_block.28.command.13: Sign itself cointains general information about character stats:
command_block.28.command.17: means Durability. General tankiness and sustain.
command_block.28.command.19: means Effects. Negative effects inflicted on your enemies.
command_block.28.command.21: means Mobility. Ways of moving around other than walking.
command_block.28.command.23: means Difficulty. Some characters are more complex than others.
command_block.28.command.24: For first time players it's better to not play
command_block.28.command.26: difficulty characters. Try learning the game with
command_block.28.command.30: ones for your first few games.
command_block.28.command.32: Taking down your enemies and capturing Altars (if you play on Altar Control map) grants you points. The first team to reach set amount of points WINS - IT'S THAT SIMPLE! Work together with your team to outplay your opponents, or if you prefer to, play for yourself and destroy anyone on your way. With many characters and hundreds of possible team compositions there is much to see, I assure you.
command_block.28.command.35:
- There are many characters and many maps. Try everything at least once and find who you like to play the most.
- Playing to win and tryharding are two different things. 
- Every character has some learning curve and things to learn. Don't expect to be good at the game instantly.
- Be sure to read detailed description in-game. These aren't too long, I promise.
- If everything is OP then nothing is. Weird balance philosophy but hey as long as it works...
